summary:
Jungkook 「you return his sweater because ‘it doesn’t smell like him’ anymore」
🤧🤧💞💓 uwu uwu soft jungkook coming through
You...
body:
Jungkook 「you return his sweater because ‘it doesn’t smell like him’ anymore」

  • 🤧🤧💞💓 uwu uwu soft jungkook coming through

You waited for Jungkook in the leaving room as he has texted you before that he’s going to be home early today. You were watching the newest episode of your favorite TV shows, hands opening your third pack of chips.

It was raining outside and there’s nothing better than being snuggled up under the fluffy blanket with dim light and your boyfriend. Right before you’re about to finish your third bag of chips, you remember boiling the water in the kitchen to brew your coffee. But instead of going to the kitchen and prepare the coffee, you went to your room, remembering you have a more important task to be done.

You opened the wardrobe and took out a white, clearly oversized sweater. It was Jungkook’s and you’ve been wearing it for quite a while before you decided to wash it yesterday.

Jungkook and you have been together for two years. He will do literally anything for you but you knew he didn’t like to share his clothes. You, on the other hand, love his clothes, they smell like him, and they give you comfort especially when he is not around. So, long story short, you’ve been wearing and washing that one sweater before eventually, finding the courage to ask another one from him.

You heard a click from the front door, and someone calling your name at the same time. You ran out of your room, leaving the sweater behind. You ran to hug him and he lifted you to the air, leaving a kiss on your lips before your feet met the ground again.

“I cook. You want to eat?”

“Actually. Yes.”

It was nothing speacial but you knew it was his favorite. He kept on talking about his day to you as you listen to him. When he stop though, all you could think about was asking him for another shirt.

“Y/n?”

“Y/n??”

“Y/n!” Jungkook snapped his finger in front of your eyes.

“Yes!”

“Did you just blank out?”

“No, no. I’m just, I just, I’m listening to you.”

“But I haven’t said anything yet.” Jungkook put down his spoon and looked at you.

“You got somethin on your mind? You can tell me? I’ll do anything except breaking up.”

“No! Really. It’s nothing important.”

“Nothing is not not important to me.”

“It’s really nothing special, Kook. We can talk about it later.” Jungkook rose from his seat and walked towards you. He started to tickle you before you knew it.

“I’ll keep on tickling you if you didn’t tell me.”

“Ya! Jungkook. HAHA. Okay, okay- I’ll tell you.” Jungkook stopped and the atmosphere suddenly tensed up.

“Actually, actually-“

“Actually?”

“Actually I, I want-“

“Actually you want?” You sighed, closing your eyes before you told me that one thing you wanted.

“Actually I want another sweater or hoodie or any clothing from you because the one you give me two weeks ago just doesn’t smell like you anymore, but I know you just don’t like people wearing your things.” You could almost hear him laughing when you said that sentence in one breath.

“Go and take that sweater to me.”

“Now?”

“Yes, love,” you quickly left the dining table and come back with the Jungkook white sweater. He asked you for it and you handed it to him.

Jungkook suddenly removed the gray hoodie he was wearing and wear the white sweater you’ve just washed instead. He raised his hand and told you to come nearer.

“Hands up,” and your body just moved automatically to his voice. He helped you to wear the gray hoodie he wears in the first place. The new hoodie was even bigger in size compared to the sweater, it covered you almost down to your knee.

“Now, that smells like me, right?”

“But, Jungkook, you don’t have to-“

“I’ll wear this one for you until it smells like me again and I’ll give it back to you. Until then, will you wear that one for me?”

“But-“

“I received no constructive criticism, and forcing you to say yes.”

You nodded your head and smiled at him, he smiled back. You could see how glad he was after he did that.

Jungkook continued eating, more carefully as he’s wearing white shirt now. Later that day, when both of you are on the couch, watching his favorite movie, although his eyes were concentrated on the movie, you could hear him whispering.

“In the future, please tell me if you want something. It’s true that I don’t like sharing clotches with people.”

“But you are more than just people to me. Way more.”

“Plus, I like how you look in my clothing.”

Jungkook 「you return his sweater because ‘it doesn’t smell like him’ anymore」

  • 🤧🤧💞💓 uwu uwu soft jungkook coming through

You waited for Jungkook in the leaving room as he has texted you before that he’s going to be home early today. You were watching the newest episode of your favorite TV shows, hands opening your third pack of chips.

It was raining outside and there’s nothing better than being snuggled up under the fluffy blanket with dim light and your boyfriend. Right before you’re about to finish your third bag of chips, you remember boiling the water in the kitchen to brew your coffee. But instead of going to the kitchen and prepare the coffee, you went to your room, remembering you have a more important task to be done.

You opened the wardrobe and took out a white, clearly oversized sweater. It was Jungkook’s and you’ve been wearing it for quite a while before you decided to wash it yesterday.

Jungkook and you have been together for two years. He will do literally anything for you but you knew he didn’t like to share his clothes. You, on the other hand, love his clothes, they smell like him, and they give you comfort especially when he is not around. So, long story short, you’ve been wearing and washing that one sweater before eventually, finding the courage to ask another one from him.

You heard a click from the front door, and someone calling your name at the same time. You ran out of your room, leaving the sweater behind. You ran to hug him and he lifted you to the air, leaving a kiss on your lips before your feet met the ground again.

“I cook. You want to eat?”

“Actually. Yes.”

It was nothing speacial but you knew it was his favorite. He kept on talking about his day to you as you listen to him. When he stop though, all you could think about was asking him for another shirt.

“Y/n?”

“Y/n??”

“Y/n!” Jungkook snapped his finger in front of your eyes.

“Yes!”

“Did you just blank out?”

“No, no. I’m just, I just, I’m listening to you.”

“But I haven’t said anything yet.” Jungkook put down his spoon and looked at you.

“You got somethin on your mind? You can tell me? I’ll do anything except breaking up.”

“No! Really. It’s nothing important.”

“Nothing is not not important to me.”

“It’s really nothing special, Kook. We can talk about it later.” Jungkook rose from his seat and walked towards you. He started to tickle you before you knew it.

“I’ll keep on tickling you if you didn’t tell me.”

“Ya! Jungkook. HAHA. Okay, okay- I’ll tell you.” Jungkook stopped and the atmosphere suddenly tensed up.

“Actually, actually-“

“Actually?”

“Actually I, I want-“

“Actually you want?” You sighed, closing your eyes before you told me that one thing you wanted.

“Actually I want another sweater or hoodie or any clothing from you because the one you give me two weeks ago just doesn’t smell like you anymore, but I know you just don’t like people wearing your things.” You could almost hear him laughing when you said that sentence in one breath.

“Go and take that sweater to me.”

“Now?”

“Yes, love,” you quickly left the dining table and come back with the Jungkook white sweater. He asked you for it and you handed it to him.

Jungkook suddenly removed the gray hoodie he was wearing and wear the white sweater you’ve just washed instead. He raised his hand and told you to come nearer.

“Hands up,” and your body just moved automatically to his voice. He helped you to wear the gray hoodie he wears in the first place. The new hoodie was even bigger in size compared to the sweater, it covered you almost down to your knee.

“Now, that smells like me, right?”

“But, Jungkook, you don’t have to-“

“I’ll wear this one for you until it smells like me again and I’ll give it back to you. Until then, will you wear that one for me?”

“But-“

“I received no constructive criticism, and forcing you to say yes.”

You nodded your head and smiled at him, he smiled back. You could see how glad he was after he did that.

Jungkook continued eating, more carefully as he’s wearing white shirt now. Later that day, when both of you are on the couch, watching his favorite movie, although his eyes were concentrated on the movie, you could hear him whispering.

“In the future, please tell me if you want something. It’s true that I don’t like sharing clotches with people.”

“But you are more than just people to me. Way more.”

“Plus, I like how you look in my clothing.”
